<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-01-31"><hi rend="italic">January 31,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 104.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge with gratification
                            the receipt of your dispatch No. 129, of the 6th instant, reporting the
                            courtesies shown Rear-Admiral Kautz and his officers of the flagship <hi rend="italic">Philadelphia</hi>, during their recent visit to
                            Guatemala city.</p>
                        <p>I am etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>